Who got b-i-n-g-o? 🙋‍♀️ These are the qualities of your passion and your purpose. While we are all students of life, there comes a time for many of us where we use what we've learned to show others the way. That's why we developed the Well-being Coach certification program, for those ready to make a career out of serving others. The training mixes wisdom practices like meditation and Ayurveda with modern research for a well-rounded approach to mind-body-spirit health and well-being. ⁠
⁠
🙏 If any of that sounds juicy, you should join our free webinar, "How to Become a Well-being Coach" – only 60 minutes of your day that could change the trajectory of your life. You can register via link in bio. ⁠

node.text:
OM has been called the sound of God humming. 😌 It's more than a chant; it's a connection to consciousness... to the ego, to the intellect and mind, to the senses and finally to the physical body and material world. ⁠
⁠
In meditation, we use OM to journey inward to reconnect to our source of pure consciousness. ✨⁠
⁠
It's like returning hOMe. Join us in the Chopra App for our new series, "From OM to Home" with our Chief Meditation Officer, Roger Gabriel, to learn more about the power of OM, and how you can use it to becOMe who you're meant to be - link in bio.

node.text:
As with happiness, peace is an inside job. 💛  Peace feels like...⁠
⁠
🔹 Breezing through your initial anger in a situation that pushes your buttons⁠
🔹 Scrolling on by when you see something on social media you don't agree with⁠
🔹 Keeping your cool in conflict by responding with compassion rather than reacting from conditioning ⁠
⁠
Our favorite way to establish this kind of equanimity is meditation, which will train your brain to bring awareness to your thoughts, making space between reality and response. Train with us in the Chopra App, where you'll find over 500 meditations to get you started – link in bio.

Vulnerability is power. Lean into the discomfort of being open and softening your edges. 🙏 In research done by Brene Brown, she found that letting yourself be seen as well as loving and serving without expectation is key to living life with a deep sense of worthiness and purpose.⁠
⁠
What is one way you can dig into vulnerability today?

node.text: @DeepakChopra serving up the truth. 🔥  They say the majority of our thoughts are recycled from the day before. Meditation allows us to take a step back and consciously decide to end this cycle, making space for the unknown and space to make a change.
